28
00:01:35,765 --> 00:01:38,373
particularly mobile phones?
And we can think of the most

29
00:01:38,373 --> 00:01:41,763
underprivileged and probably 
most need of assistance

30
00:01:41,812 --> 00:01:43,711
who are those who don't have
access to technology.

31
00:01:43,711 --> 00:01:46,421
Think of women, think of younger groups.

32
00:01:46,421 --> 00:01:48,870
Think of the elderly,
think of the disabled.

33
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:52,361
We cannot assume because mobile phone
is pretty much ubiquitous,

34
00:01:52,361 --> 00:01:56,560
that that actually affects
and people have access equally.

35
00:01:56,791 --> 00:01:59,491
When we talk about technologies
for disaster response

36
00:01:59,491 --> 00:02:02,893
and disaster management,
I think one of the first things

37
00:02:02,893 --> 00:02:06,853
that we need to take into consideration
from my community's perspective is

38
00:02:06,853 --> 00:02:11,412
how people are able to access energy
and how to reconnect

39
00:02:11,412 --> 00:02:12,950
within their own communities.

40
00:02:12,950 --> 00:02:16,452
Something that has emerged
as a big issue, finally,

41
00:02:16,452 --> 00:02:19,731
within the humanitarian sector is the role
of energy and connectivity

42
00:02:19,731 --> 00:02:22,183
as form of aid in their own right.

43
00:02:22,305 --> 00:02:25,582
So we can talk as much as we want
about access to mobile technology,

44
00:02:25,582 --> 00:02:28,047
about smartphones,
the internet of things,

45
00:02:28,047 --> 00:02:30,857
but if people, at the time
when they need it the most,

46
00:02:30,857 --> 00:02:34,376
cannot trust the mobile phones--
they cannot connect to the outside world--

47
00:02:34,376 --> 00:02:37,147
I think we are certainly 
missing a big important point.

48
00:02:37,147 --> 00:02:39,400
We need to increasingly,
more and more,

49
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:43,708
look into the role of energy connectivity 
and how we can provide energy

50
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:47,579
and connectivity as an enabling factor
for people to be able to coordinate,

51
00:02:47,579 --> 00:02:51,287
to start organizing their response,
to communicate with the outside world.

52
00:02:51,733 --> 00:02:55,612
When we look at technologies
for disaster response

53
00:02:55,612 --> 00:02:57,684
and disaster management,

54
00:02:57,684 --> 00:03:02,003
we are looking into
the latest emerging technology,

55
00:03:02,003 --> 00:03:04,404
we are looking about
the Internet of things,

56
