91
00:05:16,742 --> 00:05:23,218
but since the earthquake in Haiti
in 2010, we saw an emerging group

92
00:05:23,218 --> 00:05:30,280
of volunteer and technical communities
that crafted this new way of working,

93
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:33,831
what is known as crowd sourcing.

94
00:05:34,221 --> 00:05:38,232
So communities online 
that put themselves to tasks

95
00:05:38,232 --> 00:05:42,172
to try to really help communities
in need of assistance.

96
00:05:42,911 --> 00:05:46,200
Social media is transforming-- 
has transformed-- the world.

97
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,611
Network collaboration,
which is the backbone of the internet,

98
00:05:49,611 --> 00:05:53,730
is really transforming the way 
we communicate across the globe,

99
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:57,419
the way we are able to access knowledge,
the way we are able to share our opinions,

100
00:05:57,419 --> 00:06:00,540
the way we are able to prepare,
respond and recover

101
00:06:00,540 --> 00:06:04,439
from natural disasters
and conflict situations.

102
00:06:04,842 --> 00:06:09,799
I think the question is still,
when it gets to social media,

103
00:06:09,799 --> 00:06:13,264
is the amount of data 
which is circulating every single day

104
00:06:13,264 --> 00:06:14,613
all around the world,

105
00:06:14,613 --> 00:06:17,003
in terms of Tweets,
