is not going to accommodate everybody.

149
00:08:31,462 --> 00:08:34,143
It is important that we 
understand how people use

150
00:08:34,143 --> 00:08:36,583
technologies and what technologies 
they use and what technologies

151
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:37,708
they trust.

152
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:40,574
We just cannot assume 
that in this country,

153
00:08:40,574 --> 00:08:43,788
this is going to be the most 
used technology.

154
00:08:43,788 --> 00:08:46,664
I think we can assume,
but it is important that we understand

155
00:08:46,664 --> 00:08:48,302
as well some of those nuances.

156
00:08:48,302 --> 00:08:52,293
Particularly the social cultural 
implications of using modern technologies

157
00:08:52,293 --> 00:08:55,003
and who falls and who doesn't fall
through the digital cracks

158
00:08:55,003 --> 00:08:57,773
through the gender divide 
and so on and so forth.


159
00:08:57,773 --> 00:09:00,324
I think there's an interesting role
for academia.

160
00:09:00,324 --> 00:09:03,891
We're looking at social scientists as well,
looking into helping us understand as well

161
00:09:03,891 --> 00:09:10,173
some of these anthropological issues
with regard to how people use technology

162
00:09:10,173 --> 00:09:13,193
and how people understand information
and how they communicate.

163
00:09:13,193 --> 00:09:15,303
